<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-06-06T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-06-06T10:00:00-05:00" n="505" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d505">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/11716:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Leopoldville</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Mallon</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Leopoldville</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-06-06T16:00:00+01:00">June 6,
                                    1941—4 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received June 6—1:46 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>The High Commissioner of Free French Africa<note n="44a" xml:id="d505fn44a">Gen. Marie Eugene Adolphe Sicé.</note> confirms
                            radio broadcasts from New York that Vichy forces have established
                            wireless station and bases at N’Guimi and Zinder, Niger Colony, and that
                            German forces are now occupying Murzuch in Libya. He believes that an
                            attempt may be made to cut the line of supply from Nigeria to Egypt
                            through Fort Lamy and El Fasher. He says that the Free French forces
                            will defend the Chad but have very little equipment.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Mallon</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>